comment.author: 41909278@N08
comment._content:
A poor but interesting print of an accident scene (the prop is very obviously bent). The aircraft is 42-44___, making it either an AT-6C-10NT or AT-6C-15NT, depending on the three remaining illegible numbers. It carries the numerals '00' on the cowl and a non-standard blade antenna on the rear fuselage.

Doug MacPhail
